      "description": "Five operating points spanning flow rates 3–8 L/min and impeller speeds 2000–4000 RPM at 37°C. Inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg; outlet pressure 80–120 mmHg. Hemolysis index threshold: NIH < 0.05 g/100 L per the ASTM F1841 protocol. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-saline) used for benchtop validation; porcine blood used for confirmatory in-vitro runs."
    }
  },
